<br>
What do the rest of you think?  As for the planning, it would not be too difficult, as we would only really need a meeting time.  Once all showed up, we could then distribute as per level.  It is hard to pre-plan for something level-based when no one really knows who can actually make it until the event happens.<br>
<br>
Anyway, lets hash this out,<br>
<br>
Raloth <p><img src=http://www.canadiancommentary.com/yinyang.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#8B4513>(3/25/01 12:46:10 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Battle of the best</span><hr size=1> Another thing we could do is get the entries of all that are interested.  Then, when we can set up the brackets and who fights who.  When they are on-line they can meet somewhere and duel it out, then post to the msg board who won.  That way if we couldn't meet at once the tournament could still happen.  It would maybe happen over the span of a week or so, but that wouldn't be too bad.<br>
<br>
Just a thought.  I am interested with both my guys...<br>
<br>
Grogguk 18 warr<br>
Ferrum 11 warr<br>
<br>
